Spokesman for DPRK FM on Contact between Heads of DPRK and U.S. Dels 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 10 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry gave the following answer to a question put by KCNA Sunday as regards the contact made between the heads of the DPRK and the U.S. delegations to the six-party talks.
 As already reported, the contact between the heads of the DPRK and the U.S. delegations to the six-party talks was made in Beijing and an agreement on the resumption of the talks was reached there on July 9. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resumption of the six-party talks that have remained deadlocked for over one year is entirely thanks to the sincere efforts made by the DPRK for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the DPRK repeatedly clarified, it is the ultimate goal of the DPRK to denuclearize the Korean Peninsula and it is its consistent stand to attain the goal through dialogue and negotiations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Proceeding from this stand, the DPRK actively initiated the six-party talks and set forth realistic and constructive proposals at the last three rounds of talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has neither opposed nor given up the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks have been deadlocked till now because the U.S. refused to recognize its dialogue partner and destroyed their groundwork. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the meantime, the DPRK has clarified more than once through a series of contacts made between the DPRK and the U.S in New York that the talks can be resumed if the U.S. rebuilds their groundwork by recognizing the sovereignty of the DPRK and making clear its will for non-aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A special mention should be made of the fact that delegates of the DPRK Foreign Ministry and the U.S. Department of State met in New York from June 30 to July 1 and exhaustively negotiated the issue of providing the DPRK with a justification for returning to the six-party talks and reached a consensus of views on the matter in the main. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accordingly, the U.S. side at the contact made between the heads of both delegations in Beijing Saturday clarified that it would recognize the DPRK as a sovereign state, not to invade it and hold bilateral talks within the framework of the six-party talks and the DPRK side interpreted it as a retraction of its remark designating the former as an "outpost of tyranny" and decided to return to the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As seen above, the resumption of the talks has been possible only thanks to the principled and independent stand and tireless and sincere efforts of the DPRK side for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The outcome of the DPRK-U.S. contact clearly proves that it is possible to settle any problem when the parties concerned directly come out to solve it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The neighboring countries supporting the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and those related to it have also made efforts for the resumption of the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But Japan has done nothing for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resumption of the talks itself is important but the most essential thing is for the talks to have an in-depth discussion on ways of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula to make substantial progress in the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will do its utmost for it.

World Population Day Observed in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 10 (KCNA) -- Diversified activities have been conducted in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea to mark the World Population Day, July 11, according to this year's theme "equality".
 A photo exhibition opened at the Grand People's Study House for the purpose of enhancing public interest in population and its development, and sex equality. And mass media are calling for respecting the women in society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, seminars on reproductive health have taken place in local areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Institute of Population has sponsored a symposium, lecture and other events with a view to solving the population issue to meet the demand of the people for independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Hyok, an official of the institute, said in an interview with KCNA that July 11 this year is the 20th anniversary of the start of cooperation of the UN Population Fund with the DPRK and is also the 20th anniversary of the institute. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He voiced the willingness of the institute to strengthen relations with the UN Population Fund and other international organizations in the efforts to develop the country's population in a consonant and balanced way.

Reception Given by Chinese Charge d'Affaires 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 10 (KCNA) -- Chinese Charge d'Affaires a.i. here Guan Huabing gave a reception at the embassy on Saturday evening on the occasion of the 44th anniversary of the signing of the DPRK-China Treaty of Friendship, Cooperation and Mutual Assistance.
 Speaking at the reception, Guan Huabing said that the two parties and two governments of China and the DPRK have cooperated in various fields including politics, economy and culture in the spirit of the treaty for the last 44 years, thus making a great contribution to the prosperity of the two countries and regional peace and stability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The undying feats performed by President Kim Il Sung, the great leader of the Korean people and a close friend of the Chinese people, and the leaders of the elder generation of China for the development of the friendly relations between the two countries will always remain recorded in history and shine long, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed conviction that the Sino-Korean friendly and cooperative relations will bloom more beautifully under the deep concern of General Secretary Hu Jintao and General Secretary Kim Jong Il and thanks to the concerted efforts of the two sides. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the leadership of Kim Jong Il the fraternal Korean people are working hard to significantly greet the 60th anniversaries of the foundation of the Workers' Party of Korea and the liberation of Korea, in single-minded unity, he noted, adding that the Chinese people sincerely wish the Korean people greater success in the economic construction and the work to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, addressing the reception, said that the treaty has given strong impetus to socialist construction in the two countries and made a great contribution to ensuring peace and security in Northeast Asia for the last decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that in recent years the supreme leaders of the two countries have reached the common understanding of steadily consolidating and developing the traditional DPRK-China friendship at a series of meetings and talks, he said that the two countries are comprehensively expanding and developing the bilateral relations in the political, economic, cultural and all other fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Chinese government and people are registering great achievements in the efforts to build a comprehensively well-off society, a task laid down by the 16th Congress of the Communist Party of China, under the leadership of the CPC with Hu Jintao as its general secretary, he said, and stressed: We will as ever join the Chinese comrades in making every possible effort to boost the DPRK-China friendship as required by the new century and thus positively contribute to advancing the socialist cause in the two countries and ensuring peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world.

