Anniv. of Demise of Kim Il Sung Commemorated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Remembrance concerts and meetings and other functions were held in different parts of the country on the occasion of the 11th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung.
 The participants in the concerts sang with deep emotion the immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Il Sung," famous songs "Nostalgia," "Song of Anti-Japanese War," "Song of the River Amnok," "Phophyong Ferry" and so on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stages were songs, poems and instrumental music including "Let's Sing of the Fork Where the Road to Mangyongdae Branches Off" and "We Always Remember All Sorts of Hardships Undergone by the Leader" reflecting the President's noble intention of "believing in the people as in Heaven" and the great happiness and worthwhile life the Korean people enjoy under his loving care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their repertoires also included songs such as "Leader Is Always with Us," "Song of the Sun Will Last Forever," "Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il Are Just the Same" and "The General Steers New Century." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Remembrance meetings and oath-taking gatherings were held by working people's organizations in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Speakers there recollected with deep emotion the undying exploits Kim Il Sung performed by hewing the untrodden path of the revolution in the grim years of the 20th century and always leading the Korean revolution to victory and the boundless loving care shown by him for the people from all walks of life and took a solemn oath to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A remembrance meeting was held at the Songdowon International Children's Camp with tens of thousands of school youth and children in Wonsan City attending and evenings yearning for Generalissimo Kim Il Sung were held at children's camps in different parts of the country. Similar functions took place at schools at all levels. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials of local Party and power bodies and working people's organizations, those who had the honor of being received by the President, related persons, working people and school youth and children.

Belorussian Youth Association for Study of Juche Idea and Songun Policy Formed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- The Belorussian February 16 Youth Association for the Study of the Juche Idea and Songun Policy was inaugurated with due ceremony in Minsk on June 19. 
 The inaugural ceremony first adopted a congratulatory letter to leader Kim Jong Il on the occasion of the 41st anniversary of his start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony elected its chairman and scientific secretary general and chose "Forward with Songun! Let's establish Juche in the state administration!" as the slogan of the association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the association in his report noted that Belorussian young folks have deeply studied the Juche idea and the Songun policy in a diverse manner in close touch with the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Songun Policy in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the significance of the formation of an independent organization for the study of the Juche idea and the Songun policy in Belarus, as required by the reality, the chairman stressed the need for the newly formed association to successfully fulfill its duty.

Month of Int'l Solidarity with Korean People Opens in Mexico
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- An opening ceremony of the month of international solidarity with the Korean people was held by the Mexican Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification on June 24.
 On display in the venue of the opening ceremony were photos showing the Songun revolutionary leadership exploits performed by leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Alejandro Rosales Sanchez, chairman of the committee, in his speech at the ceremony noted that President Kim Il Sung led the three-year long Fatherland Liberation War to victory with his outstanding strategy and tactics, thus honorably defending the country's sovereignty and national dignity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo, the 10-Point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the five-point policy for national reunification put forward by Kim Il Sung are the most reasonable and just proposals for Korea's reunification, he said:  Kim Jong Il has energetically led the struggle for the country's reunification under the banner of Songun and the inter-Korean joint functions were held in Korea on the occasion of the fifth anniversary of the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called upon the Mexican people to express full support and solidarity with the Korean people in their efforts to achieve the country's reunification and struggle against the war moves of the U.S. against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of solidarity to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

Japanese FM's Reckless Remarks under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Reunification Solidarity of south Korea reportedly released a commentary on July 5 blasting the reckless remarks by the Japanese foreign minister as regards the six-way talks.
 The commentary referred to the fact that Japanese Foreign Minister Machimura at an interview with Reuters on July 4 said that Japan would reach the limit of patience sooner or later with the issue of the DPRK. It continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has so far obstructed the resumption of the six-way talks in various ways. It was so ridiculous as to talk nonsense not relevant to the agenda even at the negotiating table, chilling the atmosphere of the talks. Does Japan have the face to talk about the talks? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The patience of the Korean nation with Japan's impudent behavior has already gone beyond its limit. If Japan persistently goes reckless and does harm to the Korean people, backed by the U.S., it will only invite colder treatment, bitterer ridicule and catastrophic consequences.

Adherence to Three Principles of National Reunification Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- The Youth and Students Solidarity of south Korea to Implement the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration reportedly made public a statement on July 4 on the occasion of the 33rd anniversary of the publication of the July 4 joint statement. 
 The statement said that the June 15 joint declaration based on the three principles of national reunification is a declaration for great national unity as it calls upon all the fellow countrymen to unite and actively turn out in the movement to achieve the country's reunification under the banner of "By our nation itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It went on: The June 15 joint declaration is a declaration for national independence, for peace against war and for great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The past five years since its publication have been a period which witnessed a turn as the 70 million Koreans appeared as a driving force for national reunification along the road indicated by the joint declaration to cause the barrier of division to collapse. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The grand reunification march of the whole nation advancing on the three principles of national reunification has already begun and the prospect of reunification is bright. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the hearts of youth and students are strongly beating in the hope of acting the master to achieve national reunification, the statement called upon all the young folks to strictly abide by the three principles of national reunification for independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity.

GNP's Human Rights Racket Flailed
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- 24 different organizations in south Korea including the Reunification Solidarity, the Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration, the Headquarters of the Movement for Reunified Korean Nation, the Catholic Human Rights Committee, the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions, the National Federation of Peasants Associations and the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils reportedly issued a joint statement on July 4 assailing the Grand National Party for kicking up a noisy racket over the "human rights performance" in the north. 
 A bill submitted to the Reunification, Foreign Affairs and Trade Committee of the National Assembly by the GNP group on June 27 signified a unilateral interference in the affairs of the DPRK, a sovereign state, and is peppered with poisonous clauses meant to block the non-governmental exchange and cooperation between the south and the north, the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bill lacks any justification and validity as is the case with the "North Korean Human Rights Act" enacted by the U.S., the statement noted, adding that it was a political offensive aimed at provoking and pressurizing the north with the human rights issue as a card. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We human rights, peace and reunification movement organizations are opposed to the NA passage of the bill, the statement said, urging the need for the GNP to cancel the bill without delay.

All Koreans Called upon to Remain True to Three Charters for Nat�fl Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- The three principles of national reunification, the ten-point programme for the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo are the three charters for national reunification. They are an undying great programme for reunification that should thoroughly be implemented to accomplish the cause of national reunification. Rodong Sinmun Saturday observes this in a signed article. 
 The charters indicate the most fair and reasonable ways of achieving national reunification as early as possible in conformity with the actual conditions of the country and the unanimous desire of the Korean nation, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three principles of national reunification -- independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity -- are the cornerstone of national reunification as they clarify the fundamental standpoint and ways of solving the issue of national reunification by the concerted efforts of the Koreans according to their will and interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ten-point program for the great unity of the whole nation comprehensively lays down the goals and ideological basis, principles and ways of great national unity. It, therefore, serves as a political programme for strengthening the driving force for national reunification by achieving the unity of the whole Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The proposal for founding the DFRK indicates basic ways of achieving the reunification of the country most fairly and smoothly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three charters for national reunification reflect the spirit of national independence, the spirit of regarding the sovereignty and dignity of the nation as life and soul, and serve as an effective and just programme for reunification based on the noble patriotic desire to peacefully reunify the country by achieving the reconciliation of the north and the south and great national unity. They are enshrined in the hearts of the 70 million Koreans as the three pillars of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans in the north, the south and overseas should wage a dynamic struggle to achieve the cause of the independent and peaceful reunification of the country by their concerted efforts only on the basis of the three charters for national reunification under whatever situation and circumstances.

Stronger Unity in Songun Revolution Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- The present era in which leader Kim Jong Il's Songun politics has been pursued in all fields marks a golden era in the history of the unity in the Korean revolution. The unity in the Songun revolution serves as a banner for winning eternal victory in the revolutionary cause of Juche. Rodong Sinmun Saturday says this in a signed article.
 The unity in the Songun revolution constitutes the highest form of the unity in thinking and purpose, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unity in the Songun revolution is a fundamental factor of speeding up the new revolutionary advance in all fields of the revolution and construction in the 21st century and serves as a source of strength making it possible to win one victory after another in the fierce battle without a gun report to defend socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This unity is characterized by solid unbreakable unity and perfect one in thinking and purpose because all the servicepersons and people are united close in thinking and purpose on the basis of the monolithic revolutionary idea of their leader and it is based on the Songun idea of Juche, the great revolutionary idea in our era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unity in the Songun revolution has become the strongest unity because the monolithic and pure Songun idea prevails throughout the party and the society.
 The revolutionary ranks of Songun are replete with the revolutionary idea of Kim Jong Il, the Songun idea of Juche. "Let's share the will with our General to the last!" This has become the unanimous desire of the army and people of the DPRK dynamically stepping up the general march for Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can break the unity in the Songun revolution. It has become noble comradely unity and perfectly organized unity and represents a community linked with the same destiny in which the leader and the entire army and people share destiny to the last thanks to this perfect ideological purity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The single-minded unity achieved by the DPRK under the banner of the Songun idea is the most solid comradely unity and represents the perfectly organized entity in which all the soldiers and people move as one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The great revolutionary trait prevalent in the society, the trait of helping and leading each other forward under the slogan "One for all and all for one!" is unthinkable apart from the community of thinking, purpose and desire. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Comradely unity is as dear as life and soul to the servicepersons and people in the DPRK. Though they cannot live as affluently as others, they will not barter their worthwhile life for anything because they live amidst the mutual trust and love as Songun revolutionary comrades who share the same idea and intention with their leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the servicepersons and people move as one, prompted by the common desire as they share the same idea and intention in the society. Once an appeal is made by the leader, they will rise as one to respond to it and once the Party determines, they will flatten even a mountain. This is the revolutionary stamina of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The single-minded unity of the DPRK is the broadest-based revolutionary unity of the entire society and all the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The leader and all the people in the DPRK form an integral whole based on the single-minded unity and an unbreakable community linked with the same destiny. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No matter how desperately the U.S. imperialists and the reactionaries may try to separate the headquarters of the revolution from the Korean people, they can never break the single-minded unity of the DPRK as solid as an invulnerable fortress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article underscores the need to steadily inherit the history and tradition of the great single-minded unity of the Workers' Party of Korea, which has considered ideology as a lifeline, in the march under the banner of Songun in the new century, and goes on:
 The history of unity of the Korean revolution teaches a precious truth that ideological work should not be allowed to abate under whatever conditions and environment. Unshakable is the stand of the WPK to give priority to the ideological revolution no matter how the situation may change and no matter what others may say. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The banner of the unity in the Songun revolution is the banner which should be invariably upheld on the road of revolution rain or shine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean revolution is sure to always triumph now that Kim Jong Il clearly indicates the road to be followed in the new century and there is the unity in the Songun revolution in which all the servicepersons and people are rallied rock-solid around the leader with the monolithic idea and purpose.

Contacts between Heads of DPRK and U.S. Delegations to Sixth-Party Talks Made
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- DPRK Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Kye Gwan and U.S. Assistant Secretary of State Christopher Hill, who are heads of their countries' delegations to the six-party talks, met in Beijing on July 9. 
 The U.S. side clarified its official stand to recognize the DPRK as a sovereign state, not to invade it and hold bilateral talks within the framework of the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK side interpreted the U.S. side's expression of its stand as a retraction of its remark designating the former as an "outpost of tyranny" and decided to return to the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both sides agreed to open the fourth round of the six-party talks in the week which begins on July 25, 2005.

Kim Hyong Jik, Pioneer of Proletarian Revolution in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- July 10 is the 111th birth anniversary of Kim Hyong Jik, an indomitable revolutionary of Korea.
 On this occasion the Korean people are recollecting the immortal exploits performed by him, who pioneered in developing the nationalist movement into a proletarian revolution and thus made a great contribution to the anti-Japanese national liberation movement and brought about the dawn of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyong Jik, who was born into a patriotic family, embarked upon the road of revolution after the country was put under the military occupation of the Japanese imperialists and conducted energetic activities as a pioneer and leader of the national liberation movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After leaving school halfway in the spring of Juche 2 (1913) he, as a career revolutionary, was engrossed in making preparations for forming a new revolutionary organization which would lead the anti-Japanese national liberation movement in a unified way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His tireless efforts resulted in the formation of the Korean National Association (KNA) at the historic Pyongyang meeting on March 23, 1917. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KNA was the anti-Japanese clandestine revolutionary organization greatest ever in scale in the period just before and after the March First Popular Uprising in Korea.
 Kim Hyong Jik reviewed the nationalist movement in a critical way from the first days of his revolutionary activities. While trying to find out a way for developing anew the anti-Japanese national liberation movement, he was strongly convinced that only the proletarian revolution, an armed struggle of the popular masses, was a way for achieving the independence of the country and the freedom and emancipation of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, basing himself on a deep-going analysis of the changing situation and the lesson drawn from the failure in the March First Popular Uprising, convened the Chongsudong meeting in July 1919 and proved the historical inevitability of the proletarian revolution. At the Kuandian meeting held in August that year, he set forth a new policy on developing the anti-Japanese national liberation movement from the nationalist movement into the proletarian revolution and expounded tasks and ways for its implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The switchover was a historic event in the development of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The desire of Kim Hyong Jik for national liberation was realized successfully by President Kim Il Sung.
